{
  "stem": "1338.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nothing measures up to the courage of my cousin, Lillian, who can, for two months, refuse to take anything but water in order to save her mother without letting her know and then burn up.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean-- Because courage is an event.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, when we talk about courage today-- about what we hear about, whether it's in civilian life or in military life-- it's always an act, an act of a few minutes.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, you do something.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's very courageous.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Sometimes-- sometimes knowingly, sometimes maybe instinctively.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Whatever it is, it's courage.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it's a short.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Do you know what it means to be two months without food when you're already hungry to begin with?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I think that this kind of courage-- sorry-- is-- you cannot compare it to any other form of courage.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is like a mother, you know, that, you know, a person who raises children realizes that, you know, raising children is not giving orders but to be with children and to take the good and the bad and being always there.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's that kind of a devotion that is really measured as a real devotion, not somebody being devoted by writing a nice letter or saying something nice.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Same thing here.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Courage is not measured by an event that happens one minute, but an event that can go on for so long.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I left on the 19th of August, 1944.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The liquidation started at the end of July.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was crystal clear that we were going to be liquidated, and that everybody will be deported.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't know where exactly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we had inklings that it's not going to be a good thing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And for two weeks, my mother and I went to the plant where I worked.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was a building.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
